text: I called the day before to ask about my delivery. I was told to just show up. No appointment was needed. I arrived and called receiving and no one answered. I waited for over five minutes. An employee pulled up behind me and let me in the parking lot. Receiving told me to back into a door. Then changed their mind. They said they would call me. They never did. After 2.5 hours I walked over there. They told me go ahead and back into the door. The one bright spot was they unloaded me quickly. But then they left 4 pallets on my trailer for me to dispose of. They should have taken them. I would not want to deliver here again.

Difficult process. Weigh your trailer when coming in, has to be in just the perfect spot to be okay. Tandems must be all the way forward. Finally drop your trailer, then go to the adjoining property for empty trailers or loaded.
Oh, and the load we had going out should've been ready yesterday evening. No one knows why it's not ready, of course. But predicted to not be ready until tonight at 1700. This was a JIT load to Ohio tomorrow afternoon. Smh.

name: Bryan Johnson
text: I've been here before, they aren't the fastest in the world. One thing: if you follow your GPS it may take on a route in which some streets may not be truck routes. Make it easy. Take I-65, get off at exit 8(it's a Love's at that exit) if going north bound on 65 turn right, if south bound turn left. You'll cross railroad tracks and got through a couple of lights. Once you see Prichard Rd, turn right. It's an old gas station on the right hand corner. You better swing wide because it's a tight turn. Once you turn onto Prichard, it turns into Mobile St and you'll see the signs for shipping and receiving

name: Derek Waggoner
text: Average.  Not great not terrible.  Appt for unload 011:00 arrived 010:30 in dock by 010:45. Started unloading soon as i bumped.  Unloading docks only 3 and very tight to each other but plenty of room to line up.  Paved entrance for unload, gravel entrance for load.  Go through onsite scale first while pulling in for unload and watch for green light.  If coming from the directions given on the recording from I65, springhill ave, to mobile st pay attention. Springhill left onto mobile is tight left. I recommend taking the turn lane plus half the the other.  mobile will branch to the left on a right handed curve to stay on mobile.
